comment: Global offset is -1.5 to compensate glass-supported homing procedure. Printing of only first layer of GelMA with 1x construct. Almost nothing visible on printhead except for small, thin, very soft/slimy gel layer -> ink contains LAP. Offset problem instead?
next steps: Increase global offset to check if this is the cause for crappy prints.

comment: Global offset is -1.0. Printing of only first layer of GelMA with 1x construct. Print better visible on printhead but ill-defined and very soft/slimy. Also slimy pieces of it in ink vat which are baked stuck there. No offset problem but ink is problem. It seems to be less reactive than it should be.
next steps: Increase exposure time of GelMA ink from 30 to 60 s.

comment: Global offset is -1.0. Printing of only first layer of GelMA with 1x construct. Print well visible on printhead, complete, well-defined and not slimy. Nothing in ink vat -> T220509-4 is less reactive than it should be -> longer exposure times needed
next steps: Continue bioprinting with remaining cell-laden inks (see Log220510-01).
